title: Eat Your Vegetables! Those Poor People In Europe Don’t Have Any
text:
After visiting all three supermarkets in his hometown of Lanark, Scotland, Scott Paget sent out an SOS.
“If you have a courgette I am interested,” he tweeted last Friday after turning unsuccessfully to Facebook in his search. The green, tubular vegetable, also known as zucchini, started disappearing from grocery-store aisles across Britain early last month.
